timelineItems.text: Jay Heaps decision to rest @2Fast2Farrell Wednesday is certainly paying off right now. #NEvDC

timelineItems.name: Jeffrey Wiegand
timelineItems.text: Why not take off a defender? It's not like 9v11 is dangerous. #dcu

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: Doyle didn't play well & killed a lot of attacks, but #DCU is playing 2 DMs against 9 men. That's not the right move.

timelineItems.name: YUNG TOMMY GUN
timelineItems.text: GOALLLLLLLLLLL #DCU

timelineItems.name: Ata Dizdar
timelineItems.text: Arrieta finally brings the score level for DC United. It's 1-1 now and DC has plenty of time to get the winner over New England. #dcu

timelineItems.name: Joe
timelineItems.text: Kemp > Korb all day. #dcu

timelineItems.name: Katie Mattaini
timelineItems.text: That was just a matter of time. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Mike Madden
timelineItems.text: Nice goal, but I don't know if you get style points for scoring when you've got two more players than the other team. (Get another!) #dcu

timelineItems.name: NESoccerToday.com
timelineItems.text: Unsurprisingly, the second half possession stats look pretty ugly for #NERevs #NEvDC #DCU http://t.co/QfKhF7oRXz

timelineItems.name: Justin Churchill
timelineItems.text: Farrell was a little flat on the goal, but wrong of Shuttleworth to pass the blame on him. #NERevs #MLS #DCU

timelineItems.name: The Bolivian Yank
timelineItems.text: Wow. Coria on and maybe off in just under 10mins?? #DCU

timelineItems.desc: Perry Kitchen (D.C. United) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Perry Kitchen booked for clipping Teal Bunbury as he rushed towards the goal

timelineItems.name: Greg_YNWA1
timelineItems.text: Kemp still has acres of space out wide. Get him the ball! #DCU

timelineItems.name: RDFC
timelineItems.text: Games like #NEvDC remind me why it was a good call to get @mls Live. Wouldn't be able to watch this otherwise.

timelineItems.desc: Jermaine Jones (New England Revolution) is shown the yellow card.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Jermaine Jones called for yelling at the referee

timelineItems.name: Guy Yelencsics
timelineItems.text: Jones is putting the team on his back, all 8 of them. #NEvDC

timelineItems.name: Don
timelineItems.text: Give Coria this, he's demanding to be involved in this game with his movement and workrate. #DCU

timelineItems.desc: Davy Arnaud (D.C. United) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Davy Arnaud called for taking down Teal Bunbury

timelineItems.name: Kevin
timelineItems.text: New England might end this game with 8 men at this rate #DCU

timelineItems.name: The Bolivian Yank
timelineItems.text: Coria again with a moment of Brilliance taking on his man making a play out of nothing. Almost leads to a goal if not for Kitchen. #DCU

timelineItems.name: Ata Dizdar
timelineItems.text: Some might say Arnaud could've drawn a red there. #dcu

timelineItems.name: NE Revolution
timelineItems.text: Into five minutes of stoppage time. 1-1. #NERevs playing with nine men. #NEvDC

timelineItems.name: Jeffrey Wiegand
timelineItems.text: A draw on the road is usually okay against a top team but this is disappointing. #dcu

timelineItems.name: Will England
timelineItems.text: I gotta give the Revs huge props. Defending like mad and still looking to counter hard. Great Effort!! #NEvDC

timelineItems.name: Pablo Maurer
timelineItems.text: Coria has looked great tonight. Very nearly had an inch-perfect thru-all earlier this half, and that was great as well. #DCU

timelineItems.name: Catherine Bruno
timelineItems.text: This game is insane #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Sean Donahue
timelineItems.text: #DCU hardly looks like the best team in the East right now. Up two men, tons of space, and looks like they don't know what to do. #NEvDC

timelineItems.name: Kristen Fitz
timelineItems.text: 5 minutes. Anything can happen in 5 minutes. #NEvDC

timelineItems.name: DC Revs Fan
timelineItems.text: Gutsy performance from the 9 guys left on the field tonight. #NERevs

timelineItems.name: Jason
timelineItems.text: #DCU has missed DeLeon tonight. His willingness to be a passing target & tendency to play 1-2 touch soccer would have helped.

timelineItems.name: Steven Goff
timelineItems.text: D.C. United's 2-man advantage for 30+ minutes yields equalizer but no more: 1-1 draw at New England. #DCU retains 1st place
